CCB, Santander to Set Up 3.5 Billion Yuan Rural Joint Venture

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-27T12:25:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/ccb-banco-santander-to-set-up-venture-securities-times-says.html
China Construction Bank Corp. (939) ’s
board has adjusted a plan to set up a rural joint venture in
China with  Banco Santander SA (SAN) , the bank said in a statement
today to the Hong Kong stock exchange.  The venture will have an initial investment of 3.5 billion
yuan ($530 million) and CCB will hold 80.1 percent, according to
the statement. Investment in the venture will rise by an
additional 2.5 billion yuan in its second year, it said.  The investment is still waiting for regulatory approval,
according to the statement.  The two banks planned to set up a venture with registered
capital of 3 billion yuan and open 100 village banks in China,
the  China Daily  reported in January last year. CCB would take a
60 percent stake in the venture. the newspaper said, citing
people familiar with the matter it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Sanderson in Beijing at 
